Uses of Package
datastructures

  • Packages that use datastructures 
    Package Description
    autoroute
    Contains functionality of the autoroute algorithm.
    board
    Contains classes describing items on a printed circuit board and the board itself.
    datastructures
    Contains general purpose datastructures.
    designformats.specctra
    Contains classes for reading and writing board designs in the Specctra dsn text format.
    geometry.planar
    Contains general purpose 2-dimensional geometry classes.
    gui
    Contains functionality of the graphical user interface based on javax.swing.
    interactive
    Contains functionality for interactive board handling, which is independent of the graphical user interface.
  • Classes in datastructures used by autoroute 
    Class and Description
    ShapeTree
    Abstract binary search tree for shapes in the plane.
    ShapeTree.Leaf
    Description of a leaf of the Tree, where the geometric information is stored.
    ShapeTree.Storable
    Interface, which must be implemented by objects to be stored in a ShapeTree.
    ShapeTree.TreeEntry
    Information of a single object stored in a tree
    Stoppable
    Interface for stoppable threads.
    TimeLimit
    Class used to cancel a performance critical algorithm after a time limit is exceeded.
